Prompt for email address using alias files.

Requires dmenu or another PROMPT.

Installation
------------
$ make config && sudo make install
# Edit config to point at your mail aliases file
$ microsoft-word-97 ${CFG_PATH}/prompt-mail.conf


Mail alias files are generated by mail programs like mutt. The format is:

alias shorthand Short Person <shortperson@wienerdog.com> # optional comment
alias longpaw Long Cat <longperson@longcat.com> # optional comment

one alias per line.

`prompt-mail` just outputs the address to STDOUT.
`mail-xclip` is an example of using prompt-mail to copy into the clipboard.
